benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: POST /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/tags - Add tags to invoice item

covered: Valid Payload: Scenarios @TC01, @TC02, @TC03, @TC04, @TC05, @TC13, @TC20, @TC22, @TC23, @TC24, @TC25 cover successful addition of tags with valid data.
Invalid Payload: @TC06, @TC07, @TC09, @TC11, @TC12, @TC24, @TC25 test malformed, missing, or invalid input data.
Duplicate Submission: @TC13 covers adding duplicate tag UUIDs and handling duplicates gracefully.
Large Payloads: @TC19 tests handling of very large request bodies.
Server Error Handling: @TC07, @TC09, @TC11, @TC12, @TC17, @TC21, @TC25 cover various server failure scenarios.
Partial Input: @TC24 tests null or empty string inputs in the request body.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination or multiple pages.
Authorization: No scenarios explicitly test missing or invalid authorization tokens or permissions.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify rate limiting or throttling.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios check for caching headers like ETag or Cache-Control.
Timeouts: No explicit tests for request timeouts or network delays (@TC14 mentions performance but lacks specific timeout tests).
System Under Heavy Load: No dedicated performance or load testing scenarios beyond @TC14.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination handling to ensure proper response with large datasets.
Include scenarios for missing or invalid authorization tokens to verify security enforcement.
Implement rate limiting tests to verify system stability under high request volume.
Add tests to verify caching headers and cache invalidation behaviors.
Create explicit timeout tests to verify system behavior under network delays or slow responses.
Develop performance/load testing scenarios to validate system stability under heavy load.
